      <div xml:id="NA28-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu piriviṉkaṇ āṟṟāḷākiya (ET: āya) talaivikkut tōḻi colliyatu (ET: āṟṟum vaṉmai payappittatu). 2. itu kuṟai nayappu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what the confidante said to HER who did not have the strength in the time of separation.
            2. This is granting the request.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA28">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            eṉkaik koṇṭu taṉka ṇoṟṟiyun</l>
<l>            taṉkaik koṇṭe ṉaṉṉuta ṉīviyu</l>
<l>            maṉṉai pōla viṉiya kūṟiyuṅ</l>
<l>            kaḷvar pōlak koṭiyaṉ mātō</l>
<l>            maṇiyeṉa viḻitaru maruvip poṉṉeṉa </l>
<l>            vēṅkai tāya vōṅkumalai yaṭukkat</l>
<l>            tāṭukaḻai nivanta paiṅkaṇ mūṅki</l>
<l>            lōṭumaḻai kiḻikkuñ ceṉṉik </l>
<l>            kōṭuyar piṟaṅkaṉ malaikiḻa vōṉē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent3">Pressing my hands to his eyes<note place="foot">Literally: "taking my hands [and pressing [them] to his eyes".</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">and stroking my forehead with his hands</l>
<l rend="indent3">and speaking sweet things like mother</l>
<l>– [is] he really cruel like a robber,</l>
<l>the lord of the mountains glistening high on the peaks,</l>
<l rend="indent">with tops, where the bamboo with fresh eyes</l>
<l rend="indent2">from which dancing stems have sprung up</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the side of the high mountain spread with gold-like kino trees</l>
<l rend="indent4">[and] sapphire-like tumbling waterfalls tears at the running clouds?</l>
       </lg>
         </div>
